To separate the HTTP header from the response body, scan for the character sequence '\r\n\r\n' (carriage return and line feed). This sequence marks the end of the headers and the start of the response body:

```c
#include <string.h>
#include <stdio.h>

const char *extract_http_body(const char *raw_response) {
    const char *header_boundary = "\r\n\r\n";
    const char *body_start = strstr(raw_response, header_boundary);
    if (body_start) {
        return body_start + 4; /* Advance past the 4-byte boundary */
    }
    return NULL; /* Return NULL if header boundary is not found */
}
```

